  "input": {
    "kind": "cpu-run",
    "note": "DD/FD + ED prefix NONI. A DD or FD prefix immediately followed by an ED opcode acts as a 4 T NONI: the index prefix is abandoned (it selects no IX/IY half and no (IX+d) operand) and the ED instruction executes as if unprefixed. Run-to-budget so each case covers the NONI step plus the following ED instruction. Expected values are documented Z80 behavior (provenance z80-spec) for the decode rule and the FUSE 4 T NONI timing convention (as for ddfd00), corroborated by the zex-validated @zx-vibes/cpu reference. FUSE upstream has no DDED/FDED case, so this fixture is authored to close that net hole (a regeneration that routes ED into the index/base fallback decodes it as a PUSH-like base op instead). See .harness/intake-consumer-2026-06-28.md A1.",
